  • public class AudioBuffer
extends Vector

    AUDIOBUFFER

    Class that represents an AudioBuffer which is as an array of values, and for that reason it inherits from Vector class, because it is just an specialization of its parent, that is going to have an extra method in order to change the Audio Buffer volume.
